{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"9deec4de-2f81-4598-955e-13f67058ea12","content":"There's no pipeline file here, so here's the general migration guidance:\n\n### Replace `VSTest@3` with `dotnet test`\n\nMicrosoft.Testing.Platform doesn't use `vstest.console`; it builds the test runner into each test project. Use the `DotNetCoreCLI@2` task (or a plain `script` step) instead:\n\n```yaml\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >\n      --configuration Release\n      --logger \"trx;LogFileName=results.trx\"\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n```\n\n### Key changes\n\n1. **Remove** the `VSTest@3` task entirely.\n2. **Enable the new platform** in each test project (or `Directory.Build.props`):\n   ```xml\n   <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n   <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n   ```\n3. **TRX reports** — the `--logger trx` argument still works; publish them with:\n   ```yaml\n   - task: PublishTestResults@2\n     inputs:\n       testResultsFormat: VSTest\n       testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n     condition: succeededOrFailed()\n   ```\n4. **Code coverage** — `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` produces `.coverage` files. Publish with:\n   ```yaml\n   - task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n     inputs:\n       summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n   ```\n   If you need Cobertura XML (for the publish task), add the `coverlet.collector` NuGet package and use `--collect:\"XPlat Code Coverage\"` instead.\n\n### Summary\n\n| Before (VSTest@3) | After (Microsoft.Testing.Platform) |\n|---|---|\n| `VSTest@3` task | `DotNetCoreCLI@2` with `command: test` |\n| vstest.console discovers tests | Each test project is its own runner (`Exe`) |\n| TRX via task input | `--logger trx` CLI arg + `PublishTestResults@2` |\n| Coverage via task input | `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` + `PublishCodeCoverageResults@2` |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a12c97d7-4be6-4fe6-bb31-dc3b8450c4bd","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory is empty - there's no existing codebase. The user is asking a general guidance question about migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in Azure DevOps pipelines. Let me provide a concise, helpful answer.","outputTokens":668,"requestId":"680F:15FC40:740DC7:7B5211:6A044D56"},"id":"603ba8c1-9f80-484f-9e2a-5b40331aa43a","timestamp":"2026-05-13T10:07:41.227Z","parentId":"ea8b5876-bd09-4a7c-8fa7-097d3a61b8f8"}
